ratings.comment: Easy A (but you must attend lectures).  Fairly interesting topics; except take the provided info with a grain of salt.  She uses sources on current hot topics that have been proven wrong.

Between the asinine use of south park clips and the randomly dropped look I'm cool swear words,Jessica Brown leaves little useful content behind. I caught her using a Wikipedia quote in a power point sans context, never mind the fact the quote was itself flagged on Wikipedia. She is hands down the worst excuse for an instructor I've had at the UW.

She is really good at this subject. Make sure you do all the reading because its on the exams. The class grading is simple and easy just go to class and read and you can get a pretty easy A. Overall a very good class.
Amazing! Such an interesting class and an easy A

Has a refreshingly laid back style of teaching. Is funny, interesting, keeps students entertained and awake. It is easy to succeed in her class. Tests are easy to study for and straight forward. DO THE DEW- she loves Mountain Dew.

interesting subjects, cool videos and lecture materials.  easy exams.  however, she is completely unprofessional.  she swears in class, slurps soda and tells stories about her ex-boyfriend. does not treat students with respect at all, makes me very uncomfortable in the classroom.  just really really unprofessional.
Jessica is very funny and makes the topics very interesting.  I find myself WANTING to go to class.  Exams are straight forward...no text, just a lot of interesting readings.

Fantastic TA. She made every discussion so much fun and so interesting. I really feel like I learned more in discussion than in lecture. She had great ways of making us all feel comfortable speaking in class. The atmosphere was great!
